com.parse4cn1.nativeinterface

Interface ParseInstallationNative

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.codename1.system.NativeInterface

    public interface ParseInstallationNative
extends com.codename1.system.NativeInterface
    Provides access to native functionality related to Parse installations. This functionality is to be provided by native Parse SDKs.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        void initialize(java.lang.String applicationId,
                java.lang.String clientKey)
        Initializes the Parse SDK.

        This method may raise an exception, e.g., if the Parse SDK is already initialized and it is the responsibility of the caller to handle any such exceptions.

        Parameters:
        applicationId - The Parse application ID.
        clientKey - The Parse client key.

      • getInstallationId

        java.lang.String getInstallationId()
        Retrieves the installation ID of the current installation. An installation should be created on the fly and persisted to Parse if one does not exist.

        It is recommended to perform the save operation in a background thread to prevent blocking. It is up to the caller to retry if an immediate attempt to retrieve the installation using the ID returned by this method fails.

        Returns:
        The current installation's ID.
